This API provides CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing a ToDo list. The service is built with Node.js and Express and uses PostgreSQL as the database.
Base-URL: localhost:3001

# Endpoint: "/todos"

## Methods:

### GET:

Description:
Fetches all ToDo items from the database

Response:
JSON Array of ToDo objects

### POST:

Description:
Creates a new ToDo item and inserts it into the database

Response: 
JSON object of the created ToDo

# Endpoint: "/todos/:id

### PUT:

Description:
Updates the text and/or the completed status of an existing ToDo

Response:
Updated Json object of the created ToDo

### DELETE:

Description:
Deletes a ToDo from database

Response:
"message": "ToDo deleted"
